ward |first4=Annie |title=PGA Awards: '1917' Named Outstanding Motion Picture |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/producers-guild-awards-2020-winners-list-full-1269972|accessdate=January 19, 2020 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=January 18, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]'' || HBO\n|-\n| ''[[The Crown (TV series)|The Crown]]'' || Netflix\n|-\n| ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' || rowspan=\"2\"|HBO\n|-\n| ''[[Watchmen (TV series)|Watchmen]]''\n|}\n\n==Total awards by network==\n* HBO \u2013 6\n* AMC \u2013 5\n* NBC \u2013 5\n* ABC \u2013 4\n* FOX \u2013 1\n* FX \u2013 1\n* Hulu \u2013 1\n* Netflix \u2013 1\n* Showtime \u2013 1\n\n==Programs with multiple awards==\n;3 awards\n* ''[[Mad Men]]'' (consecutive)\n* ''[[The Sopranos]]''\n\n;2 awards\n* ''[[Breaking Bad]]'' (consecutive)\n* ''[[The West Wing]]'' (consecutive)\n\n==Programs with multiple nominations==\n{{col-begin}}\n\n{{col-break}}\n\n;8 nominations\n* ''[[Game of Thrones]]''\n\n;6 nominations\n* ''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]''\n* ''[[Mad Men]]''\n* ''[[The Sopranos]]''\n\n;5 nominations\n* ''[[Breaking Bad]]''\n* ''[[Dexter (TV series)|Dexter]]''\n* ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]''\n* ''[[The West Wing]]''\n\n{{col-break}}\n\n;4 nominations\n* ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]''\n* ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]''\n* ''[[House of Cards (U.S. TV series)|House of Cards]]''\n\n;3 nominations\n* ''[[Better Call Saul]]''\n* ''[[Downton Abbey]]''\n* ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''\n* ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]''\n\n{{col-break}}\n\n;2 nominations\n* ''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]''\n* ''[[Boston Legal]]''\n* ''[[The Crown (TV series)|The Crown]]''\n* ''[[The Handmaid's Tale (TV series)|The Handmaid's Tale]]''\n* ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''\n* ''[[Law & Order]]''\n* ''[[Stranger Things]]''\n* ''[[True Blood]]''\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{PGA Awards Chron}}\n{{Producers Guild of America Award for Best Episodic Drama}}\n\n[[Category:Producers Guild of America Awards]]\n", "name_user": "Felida97", "label": "safe", "comment": "(dummy edit to add to previous summary:) I just realized that for some networks (like NBC) they are counted (but not for example for CBS); I'm going to correct that and make it consistent; doesn't make sense to count them for this", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Producers_Guild_of_America_Award_for_Best_Episodic_Drama"}
{"title_page": "Violence (song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Violence\n| cover      = Grimes and i o - Violence (Alternative cover).jpg\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Grimes (musician)|Grimes]] and i_o\n| album      = [[Miss Anthropocene]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|9|5}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electropop]]|[[Trance music|trance]]|[[Rave#Rave music|rave]]-[[Pop music|pop]]|[[synth-pop]]}} <!-- Sourced in the \"Critical reception\" section -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=40}}\n| label      = [[4AD]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Grimes (musician)|Claire Boucher]]|Garrett Lockhart}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Grimes|Garrett Lockhart}}\n| chronology = [[Grimes (musician)|Grimes]]\n| prev_title = Pretty Dark\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = So Heavy I Fell Through the Earth\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{extra chronology\n | artist     = i_o\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Fatal Error\n | prev_year  = 2018\n | title      = Violence\n | year       = 2019\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n{{Extra album cover\n| header = Alternate cover\n| type = single\n| cover = Grimes and i_o - Violence.png\n| border = yes\n| caption = Original single cover\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Violence'''\" is a song by Canadian musician [[Grimes (musician)|Grimes]] and American DJ i_o. It was released on September 5, 2019, as the second single from her fifth studio album ''[[Miss Anthropocene]]''.<ref name=\"NME\"/>\n\n==Background==\nOn September 3, 2019, the singer teased the release by posting a painting of an angelic figure whose hands touch a sword pierced into a planet resembling earth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8528913/grimes-teases-new-single|title=Grimes Teases 'A New Way to Die' Single|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> She also blanked the remainder of her [[Instagram]] page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.factmag.com/2019/09/03/grimes-to-release-new-music-this-thursday/|title=Grimes to release new music this Thursday|website=[[Fact Magazine (UK)|Fact Magazine]]|last=Panzer|first=Natalia|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> The post was accompanied by the caption \"A new way to die! 2 days.\" which led publications to believe it would be the name of the song.<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-a-new-way-to-die-new-single-2544437|title=Grimes confirms new single \u2018A New Day To Die\u2019 will arrive this week|website=[[NME (magazine)|NME]]|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> However, she clarified the actual song title a day later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B2AFp-rHmtw/|title=Official press release for Violence - dropping tonight at midnight ! \u23f0|via=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> Another post in anticipation of the release read \"There were Humans and Gods and nothing but Angels in between.\"<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/grimes-drops-new-single-and-video-violence-1203324574/|title=Grimes Drops New Single and Video, \u2018Violence\u2019|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|last=Aswad|first=Jem|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nSelim Bulut of ''[[Dazed Digital]]'' described the track as \"a more ethereal piece of electro-pop, driven by a thumping kickdrum and synth arp bassline\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/45873/1/grimes-io-violence-watch-music-video|title=Grimes returns with a new single, \u2018Violence\u2019|website=[[Dazed Digital]]|last=Bulut|first=Selim|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> Jem Aswad at ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' spoke of the song as a \"synth-driven, soft-focus collaboration with DJ i_o\".<ref name=\"variety\"/> Writing for ''[[Uproxx]]'', Derrick Rossignol noted that \"it\u2019s an engaging piece of atmospheric but dance-ready electronic pop\" and compared it to some of her previous works.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/pop/grimes-violence-video/|title=Grimes Sets War To Thumping Electronic Pop In Her New \u2018Violence\u2019 Video|website=[[Uproxx]]|last=Rossignol|first=Derrick|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> In his review of Grimes' album, ''Miss Anthropocene'', Anna Richmond described \"Violence\" as a song about \"an abusive relationship, [...] only understood as being sung by the actual Earth ''to'' the very crisis of [[Global warming|climate change]]\" and, sonically, \"[[Four on the floor (music)|four-to-the-floor]] [[Trance music|trance]] with a [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]-esque vocal melody\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Richmond |first1=Anna |title=Review: Grimes' ''Miss Anthropocene'' Feels Both Deeply Personal and Communal |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review-grimes-miss-anthropocene-feels-both-deeply-personal-and-communal/ |website=[[Slant Magazine]] |accessdate=5 March 2020 |date=22 February 2020}}</ref> Rhian Daly of ''[[NME]]'' described the record as \"pulsating, intergalactic [[Rave#Rave music|rave]]-[[Pop music|pop]]\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daly |first1=Rhian |title=Grimes - 'Miss Anthropocene' review: an iconoclast continues to march to the beat of her own drum |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/grimes-miss-anthropocene-review-2612446 |website=[[NME]] |accessdate=March 16, 2020 |date=February 20, 2020}}</ref> The song appeared on ''[[Paper (magazine)|PAPER Magazine]]'''s list of the \"10 Songs You Need To Start Your Weekend Right\", where the writer, Michael Love Michael, described it as \"a bouncy [[synthpop]] track that feels like equal parts [[Britney Spears]] club hit and PSA for toxic relationships and/or climate change\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Michael Love Michael |title=Bops Only: 10 Songs You Need to Start Your Weekend Right |url=https://www.papermag.com/bops-only-kidd-kenn-2640232155.html |website=[[Paper (magazine)|PAPER]] |accessdate=7 April 2020 |date=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"Violence\" was released through Grimes' YouTube channel alongside the song's official release on September 5, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/watch-grimes-video-for-new-song-violence/|title=Watch Grimes\u2019 Video for New Song \"Violence\"|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Yoo|first=Noah|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> It was directed by Grimes herself. The video begins with the singer reading ''[[The Art of War]]'' by [[Sun Tzu]] which would predict the outcome of the video.<ref name=\"mtv\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3138130/grimes-violence-video/|title=Grimes Commands a Legion of Ninjas in 'Violence'|website=[[MTV]]|last=Alston|first=Trey|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> Later on March 15, 2020, the cover of the book got censored due to copyright claims made by that specific edition publishing company.{{Citation needed|reason=Video comments section on Youtube and video content|date=March 2020}} Grimes is then seen performing dances among a group of female warriors whose movements mimic war combats.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/grimes-violence-i-o-video-880155/|title=Watch Grimes Learn the Art of War in \u2018Violence\u2019 Music Video|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|author1=Shaffer, Claire|author2=Legaspi, Althea|author3=Zemler, Emily|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> She is dressed in a \"silver, futuristic dress\" from Iris Van Herpen's fall 2019 couture collection throughout the video.<ref name=\"mtv\"/> ''Variety'' compared the visuals to a \"a supermodel session in the 1990s\".<ref name=\"variety\"/> The video features choreography inspired by [[TikTok]] user Cindy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sanchez|first=Chelsey|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a31022820/grimes-violence-music-video-playback/|title=Grimes's Dance for the \"Violence\" Music Video Was Inspired by This TikTok|work=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=February 21, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/121193077|title=Violence / Grimes and i_o|work=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>\n* Grimes \u2013 vocals, production\n* Garrett Lockhart \u2013 production\n* [[Tom Norris (record producer)|Tom Norris]] \u2013 mixing\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4746|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=September 16, 2019|accessdate=September 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| 31\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboarddanceelectronic|19|artist=Grimes|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 3, 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Grimes}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:4AD singles]]\n[[Category:Grimes (musician) songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Violence\n| cover      = Grimes and i o - Violence (Alternative cover).jpg\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Grimes (musician)|Grimes]] and i_o\n| album      = [[Miss Anthropocene]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|9|5}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electropop]]|[[Trance music|trance]]|[[Rave#Rave mu