4/258|title=Ciclismo Mundial|work=UCI.org|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|accessdate=25 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425132540/https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/15079/2003484/258|archivedate=25 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, she won the elite race at the [[European Cyclo-cross Championships]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.eurosport.com/cyclo-cross/cyclo-cross-video-yara-kastelijn-wins-women-s-european-championship_vid1260139/video.shtml |title='Total Dutch dominance!' - Yara Kastelijn takes European title |work=EuroSport |accessdate=10 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n===Road===\n{{div col start}}\n;2015\n: 1st [[File:MaillotHolanda.svg|20px]] [[Dutch National Time Trial Championships|Time trial]], National Junior Road Championships\n: 3rd Time trial, [[2015 European Road Championships|UEC European Junior Road Championships]]\n: 8th [[2015 UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Women's junior road race|Road race]], [[2015 UCI Road World Championships|UCI Junior Road World Championships]]\n;2016\n: 1st Stage 2a ([[Team time trial|TTT]]) [[Giro del Trentino Alto Adige-S\u00fcdtirol]]\n;2017\n: 8th [[7-Dorpenomloop Aalburg]]\n;2018\n: 7th Road race, [[2018 European Road Cycling Championships|UEC European Under-23 Road Championships]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Cyclo-cross===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n;2019\u20132020\n: 1st [[File:EuropeanChampionJersey(2016).png|20px]] [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|UEC European Championships]]\n: [[2019\u201320 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Superprestige]]\n::1st [[Cyclo-cross Gavere]]\n::3rd [[Superprestige Gieten]]\n::3rd [[Cyclo-cross Zonhoven]]\n::3rd [[Superprestige Diegem]]\n: 3rd Overall [[DVV Trophy]]\n::1st [[Cyclo-cross Koppenberg|Koppenbergcross]]\n::3rd [[GP Mario De Clercq]]\n: 1st Ambiancecross\n: [[Ethias Cross]]\n::2nd [[Polderscross]]\n: 2nd [[Grand Prix Neerpelt]]\n: 2nd Cyclocross Gullegem\n: [[2019\u201320 UCI Cyclo-cross World Cup|UCI World Cup]]\n::3rd